body:
Warnings are emitted only for the localparams `CATPK_IE_BIT` and `CATPK_IE_LOGIC` below. It's odd that the other permutations detect the correct width and don't warn.
The warnings are only emitted when replicating an int enum's member which specifies a value but not the width.
IEEE looks conclusive that int should always be 32b.
```
%Warning-WIDTHCONCAT: testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat.sv:15:52: Unsized numbers/parameters not allowed in concatenations.
                                                         : ... In instance testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat
   15 | localparam bit   [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_IE_BIT   = {IE0, IE1, IE2};
      |                                                    ^
                      ... For warning description see https://verilator.org/warn/WIDTHCONCAT?v=4.215
                      ... Use "/* verilator lint_off WIDTHCONCAT */" and lint_on around source to disable this message.
%Warning-WIDTHCONCAT: testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat.sv:15:57: Unsized numbers/parameters not allowed in concatenations.
                                                         : ... In instance testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat
   15 | localparam bit   [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_IE_BIT   = {IE0, IE1, IE2};
      |                                                         ^
%Warning-WIDTHCONCAT: testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat.sv:16:52: Unsized numbers/parameters not allowed in concatenations.
                                                         : ... In instance testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat
   16 | localparam logic [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_IE_LOGIC = {IE0, IE1, IE2};
      |                                                    ^
%Warning-WIDTHCONCAT: testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat.sv:16:57: Unsized numbers/parameters not allowed in concatenations.
                                                         : ... In instance testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat
   16 | localparam logic [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_IE_LOGIC = {IE0, IE1, IE2};
      |                                                         ^
%Error: Exiting due to 4 warning(s)
```

Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
Reproduce with:  verilator --lint-only testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat.sv
```
module testcase_UnsizedEnumConcat;
typedef enum int {EE0=32'd0, EE1=32'd1, EE2=32'd2} explicitWidth_explictValue;
typedef enum int {IE0=0,     IE1=1,     IE2=2}     implicitWidth_explictValue;
typedef enum int {II0,       II1,       II2}       implicitWidth_implictValue;

localparam bit   [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_EE_BIT   = {EE0, EE1, EE2};
localparam logic [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_EE_LOGIC = {EE0, EE1, EE2};

// Warning-WIDTHCONCAT Unsized numbers/parameters not allowed in concatenations.
// IEEE 1800-2017 Table 6-8 says int and integer are 32b, so nothing should be
// ambiguous about this.
localparam bit   [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_IE_BIT   = {IE0, IE1, IE2};
localparam logic [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_IE_LOGIC = {IE0, IE1, IE2};

localparam bit   [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_II_BIT   = {II0, II1, II2};
localparam logic [2:0] [31:0] CATPK_II_LOGIC = {II0, II1, II2};

localparam bit   [31:0] UNPK_EE_BIT   [2:0] = '{EE0, EE1, EE2};
localparam logic [31:0] UNPK_EE_LOGIC [2:0] = '{EE0, EE1, EE2};
localparam bit   [31:0] UNPK_IE_BIT   [2:0] = '{IE0, IE1, IE2};
localparam logic [31:0] UNPK_IE_LOGIC [2:0] = '{IE0, IE1, IE2};
localparam bit   [31:0] UNPK_II_BIT   [2:0] = '{II0, II1, II2};
localparam logic [31:0] UNPK_II_LOGIC [2:0] = '{II0, II1, II2};

localparam int     UNPK_EE_INT     [2:0] = '{EE0, EE1, EE2};
localparam integer UNPK_EE_INTEGER [2:0] = '{EE0, EE1, EE2};
localparam int     UNPK_IE_INT     [2:0] = '{IE0, IE1, IE2};
localparam integer UNPK_IE_INTEGER [2:0] = '{IE0, IE1, IE2};
localparam int     UNPK_II_INT     [2:0] = '{II0, II1, II2};
localparam integer UNPK_II_INTEGER [2:0] = '{II0, II1, II2};

endmodule
```

